<title type="html"><![CDATA[9-30(Thu.) To be a people-pleaser/ Table topics session.(Host: Lawrence )]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=545&amp;p=568#p568"><![CDATA[
<span style="color: #FF0000">Place:</span>Zoom Meeting<br /><span style="color: #FF0000">Agenda:<br /></span>07:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />07:05-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />07:40-8:00 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited, 2 mins / each member)<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2 discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation<br /><br />Let's join the Zoom meeting this Thursday at 07:00 pm<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ... 09#success<br /><br /><span style="color: #FF0000">會議</span> ID:929 8726 6213<br /><span style="color: #FF0000">密碼</span>:112233<br /><br /><br />Session 1<br />Stop to be a people- pleaser. <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.verywellmind.com/how-to-stop-being-a-people-pleaser-5184412">https://www.verywellmind.com/how-to-sto ... er-5184412</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1. Do you think a people- pleaser is ok or not, why or why not? <br />2. Do you think a people pleaser is happy or actually not? Why?<br />3. How much are you as a people- pleaser ranking from 1 to 10? ( to your spouse, to your mom-in-law, to your boss, to your teachers, to your friends, classmates, to the tradition ----). What’s the result?<br />4. Did you ever think about changing yourself as a people pleaser?<br />5. Please share your experience or the stories you heard?<br /><br />Second session is ‘Table topic’.<br />The purpose of Table topic is to train a speaker to give an impromptu speech. <br />The host will give an example by asking someone (anyone) to ask him a question. After the host answers the question, he will ask someone else another question. After the person answers it, he will ask another question to someone else.  It’s like a relay race. So please, each participant prepares some questions in his mind. The questions can be about daily life, covid 19, cell phones , sport, daily life, current news, education, hobby, science, family, career, love relationship, -------. Speaking time will be strictly controlled. Each answer is for 2 minutes.<br />P.S.<br />1.因疫情關係，聚會方式改為線上遠距。<br />2.參加三次後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />3.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=89">AndrewWang</a> — Fri Sep 24, 2021 10:52 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
